Text.Value: Not quite. You'll see when we get there.
You made your choice.
I seem to recall you encouraging me to spare Nightsong. Perhaps you're more like me than you care to admit. Help me, or don't.

EditorData.logicalname: PLAYER ENCOURAGED SH TO SPARE NIGHTSONG

Text.Value: I hope that's true, but I'm not so sure. She has a far reach, and a long memory.
You've nothing to be sorry for. Far from it, in fact. Without your help, things could have ended very differently for me.
You mean Shar? Forget it - her spite can't hurt you now.
Shar? Not Lady Shar? Once you'd have bitten your own tongue rather than speak like that.
You blaspheme. I ought to kill you for that.
I need to take back control. Seize what I've been denied.
You want to go swimming? I was expecting something dangerous.
With your encouragement, remember?

EditorData.logicalname: PLAYER ENCOURAGED SH TO SPARE NIGHTSONG

Text.Value: I see. In that case you'd better go get some rest. Wouldn't want your focus to slip.
Well... don't laugh, but one thing I do remember about myself is that I can't swim. I think it's time I remedied that. And washed off Shar's bile at the same time.
A lot's changed since then. More than I ever thought was possible. And besides, she's no lady.
You wouldn't say that if you ever saw me in the water.
If that's what you want, I'll be ready.
Down the coast? Are we going fishing?
I have an idea, but I'll need your help.
So what do you want to do about it?
I'm sorry.
I'm no swimming teacher, just so you're aware.
I have an idea. Something I've wanted to do for a while. Something that might help me put her in the past... but I'll need your help.
Good. Until then. Get some rest while you can.
Wait until the others are asleep, then come with me. There's a place we can go, down the coast a little.

I sacrificed my memory's for Shar- to preserve my mission. But one thing I do remember about myself is that I can't swim. I think it's time I remedied that. And washed off Shar's bile at the same time.
There's no time for this.
Understood. Just keep me from drowning, and don't laugh while I flail about in waist-high water. That's all I ask.
I want to wash it away. All of it...
Just wait until the others are asleep, then come with me. There's a place we can go, down the coast a little.
I can still feel the Shadowfell all over me... still hear her words in my ear. I feel... unclean.
Of course.
No. This is no time for distractions - we need to keep focused.
What do I need to do?
I did, and its too late for regrets... but I wish I felt a little more comfortable in my own skin.
Strictly speaking you should have killed me the moment Shar banished me. But you didn't, for whatever reason. Help me, or don't.
Do you expect sympathy from me? You turned your back on the Dark Lady.
But what then? Come on, let's not start keeping secrets again.
Don't be so quick to judge - she didn't ask anything of you. Who's to say you'd have handled it any differently?
What's done is done, but I have an idea that might help me... if you're willing to play a part.
Do you remember what I told you before, about how I can't swim? Well, I think it's time I remedied that. And washed off Shar's bile at the same time.
I had thought you would want to make time for me... I suppose I was wrong. Rest well then.

Synopsis: CRD for Shadowheart on the Enemy of Shar Path inviting the avatar to a romance scene. Shadowheart is feeling vulnerable after defying her goddess and being declared a heretic. She's now enemy to her former kin, and has been 'marked' (inflicted with so much pain by Shar that her her has partially turned white). Now she concorts a plan to restore some autonomy
